<percentage>0</percentage></teachingTypeInCurriculum></teachingTypesInCurriculumYear></programCurriculum><programDescriptions><contentLink><contentSummary xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[In forencic research, there is a growing need for scientists who can combine know-how in the fields of chemistry, biology, computer science or statistics with knowledge in the fields of criminology and law. The Forensic Science study programme trains students to be innovative researchers or policy-makers who can make a contribution to the development of forensic science.]]></contentSummary><contentType>website</contentType><subject>objectives</subject><webLink xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[http://studieadres.nl]]></webLink></contentLink><contentLink><contentSummary xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[Criminal Law & Expert Evidence; the Chain of Evidence I and II; Policy, Ethics and Media; Forensic Statistics; Forensic Information Systems; Complex Crime Scenes and the Science of Collecting Trace Evidence.]]></contentSummary><contentType>website</contentType><subject>curriculum</subject><webLink xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[http://studieadres.nl]]></webLink></contentLink><contentLink><contentSummary xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[Lectures, research, branch-specific internship at an agency where forensic research plays a role.]]></contentSummary><contentType>website</contentType><subject>instruction modes</subject><webLink xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[http://studieadres.nl]]></webLink></contentLink><contentLink><contentSummary xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[All over the world forensic science is an important subject. Our programme distinguishes itself from others because it builds on general science instead of forensic science bachelors. As this is exactly the background of many employees of forensic laboratories in (also) NFP countries, our programme obtains many requests from people in these countries. The high costs are often a barrier; becoming an NFP connected programme will much help]]></contentSummary><contentType>website</contentType><subject>socio-economic contribution</subject><webLink xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[http://studieadres.nl]]></webLink></contentLink><contentLink><contentSummary xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[Many of the forensic laboratory employees are lacking sufficient academic level. Our programme, being a Research Masters, prepares students towards forensic research. When graduated our students will give qualitative impulses to their home organization. The quality, attitude and standards of the forensic laboratory personnel will thus improve]]></contentSummary><contentType>website</contentType><subject>sustainable strengthening</subject><webLink xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[http://studieadres.nl]]></webLink></contentLink><contentLink><contentSummary xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[Tuition fees are adjusted annually, for up to date information please see www.uva.nl/isp]]></contentSummary><contentType>website</contentType><subject>tuition fee</subject><webLink xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[http://studieadres.nl]]></webLink></contentLink><contentLink><contentSummary xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[The Master's programme in Forensic Science is designed to train students to become researchers with a thorough knowledge of forensics. 

Alternatively, this Master qualifies graduates for careers in research at forensic institutes or forensic investigation agencies both within and outside the Netherlands, as well as at TNO, the RIVM or with the police force. Insurance companies, courts and ministries are also expected to have an increasing need for forensic science expertise.]]></contentSummary><contentType>website</contentType><subject>job perspective</subject><webLink xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[http://studieadres.nl]]></webLink></contentLink><programDescription xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[A dead body is found in a harbour. The body is completely packed in black industrial foil, bound together with tape and weighed down with pavement tiles secured by steel cables and chains. The police decide to transport the remains undisturbed to the forensic institute.

Careful photography and recovery of the binding material is followed by a series of investigations: an autopsy, blood analysis, examination of microtraces under the fingernails, examination of the tape for fingerprints and determination of DNA samples. Later the body is identified by the tattoo on the victim's ankle, which matches the description of that on a missing person.
 
Ultimately, a physical match between the victim's broken artificial nail and a piece of it found at the suspected crime scene turns out to be a valuable clue.

Forensic Science is a complex and diverse field. An ever increasing amount of information can be obtained from an ever smaller amount of material. Scientific research yields new developments all the time, generating more advanced methods. Researchers must, therefore, be able to combine forensic expertise with sophisticated technologies in a multidisciplinary environment.]]></programDescription><programDescription xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[A dead body is found in a harbour. The body is completely packed in black industrial foil, bound together with tape and weighed down with pavement tiles secured by steel cables and chains. The police decide to transport the remains undisturbed to the forensic institute.

Careful photography and recovery of the binding material is followed by a series of investigations : an autopsy, blood analysis, examination of microtraces under the fingernails, examination of the tape for fingerprints and determination of DNA samples. Later the body is identified by the tattoo on the victim's ankle, which matches the description of that on a missing person.
 
Ultimately, a physical match between the victim's broken artificial nail and a piece of it found at the suspected crime scene turns out to be a valuable clue.

Forensic Science is a complex and diverse field. An ever increasing amount of information can be obtained from an ever smaller amount of material. Scientific research yields new developments all the time, generating more advanced methods. Researchers must, therefore, be able to combine forensic expertise with sophisticated technologies in a multidisciplinary environment.]]></programDescription><programName xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[Forensic Science]]></programName><programName xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[Forensic Science]]></programName><programSummary xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[The Research Master's programme in Forensic Science, is unique in the Netherlands. It distinguishes itself from most programmes in Forensic Science as it builds on a wide range of science backgrounds.]]></programSummary><programSummary xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[The Research Master's programme in Forensic Science, is unique in the Netherlands. It distinguishes itself from most programmes in Forensic Science as it builds on a wide range of science backgrounds.]]></programSummary><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[criminaliteit]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[forensisch onderzoek]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[strafrecht]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[beta]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[biologie]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[chemie]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[juridisch]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[medisch]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[natuurkunde]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[natuur]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[scheikunde]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[wetgeving]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[anatomie]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[fysica]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[psychobiologie]]></searchword><searchword xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[rechte